              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/52645070-prabhjot-kaur?shelf=indian">indian</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1626949144" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer3674320767108227746"><b>The Immortals of Meluha - 3 stars</b><br/><br/><b>The Secret of the Nagas - 3 stars</b><br/><br/><b>The Oath of the Vayuputras - 2 stars</b><br/><br/>This trilogy was mostly a disappointment. Although the first and the second book were okay, last one disappointed the most. While Amish Tripathi&apos;s imagination knows no bounds, I was still not impressed. Throughout the entire series I felt like, all three books were written by different authors. I&apos;m not sure why but something felt amiss. I wanted to and I really tried but I just couldn&apos;t love it </span>
  <span id="freeText3674320767108227746" style="display:none"><b>The Immortals of Meluha - 3 stars</b><br /><br /><b>The Secret of the Nagas - 3 stars</b><br /><br /><b>The Oath of the Vayuputras - 2 stars</b><br /><br />This trilogy was mostly a disappointment. Although the first and the second book were okay, last one disappointed the most. While Amish Tripathi's imagination knows no bounds, I was still not impressed. Throughout the entire series I felt like, all three books were written by different authors. I'm not sure why but something felt amiss. I wanted to and I really tried but I just couldn't love it as much as I had wanted to.<br /><br />3 stars overall.</span>
  <a data-text-id="3674320767108227746" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

