<div id="review_1936475784" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1936475784" />
    <a title="Mysticpalak" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/6785106-mysticpalak"><img alt="Mysticpalak" src="https://s.gr-assets.com/assets/nophoto/user/f_50x66-6a03a5c12233c941481992b82eea8d23.png" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1936475784?book_show_action=true">Mar 09, 2017</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Mysticpalak" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Mysticpalak" href="/user/show/6785106-mysticpalak">Mysticpalak</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1936475784" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer11600151272340771570">What has intrigued me the most about this book is the depiction of a powerful deity, Lord Shiva, in the most human way possible. It offers a whole new perspective to the Hindu mythology and how indeed the greatness of such a being eventually led him to be worshipped through time immemorial. Har Har Mahadev!</span>

          </span>
        </div>


      <div class="reviewFooter uitext buttons">
          

